[
    {
        "content": "<p>Can I have an assert macro that takes a struct and a field name and asserts that the field is structurally pinned with <code>#[pin]</code>?</p>",
        "id": 441295842,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1717008172
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I have a <em>very</em> hacky solution:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"fm\">macro_rules!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">assert_pinned</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"cp\">$ty</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"nc\">ty</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"cp\">$field</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"nc\">ident</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"cp\">$field_ty</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"nc\">ty</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">_assert_pinned</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">I</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">FnOnce</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">I</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"p\">(),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">I</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">pinned_init</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">PinInit</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">_check</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">I</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">I</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">pinned_init</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">PinInit</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"cp\">$field_ty</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"cp\">$ty</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">pinned_init</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">__internal</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">HasPinData</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">__pin_data</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">_assert_pinned</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"cp\">$field_ty</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">I</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">init</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"cp\">$field</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">init</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">});</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>do you need this as a stable thing (I recall that I commented on one of your patches that might need this)? because then I could give you a less hacky solution, but I would prefer to do this after I am able to use <code>syn</code>...</p>",
        "id": 441299121,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1717009441
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I need a solution that can go upstream and I don't want it to be blocked on syn. But you could always replace the implementation later?</p>",
